   ADDITIONAL NOTICE — RESEARCH USE ONLY

   This software is the open-source verifier for cryptographic
   commitments produced by the Peptide Rx Autonomous Thesis Loop (ATL)
   protocol. The protocol and this verifier are scoped to nonclinical
   research evaluation only.

   No output of this verifier implies a clinical claim, human safety,
   therapeutic efficacy, or compliance with any regulatory framework.

   The verifier does NOT prove that a peptide design is safe for human
   use. It proves only that the cryptographic chain of custody for a
   published design attestation is internally consistent.

   Software status: EXPERIMENTAL. APIs and protocol details are subject
   to change. The cross-language byte-identical property is locked on
   the published test vectors; everything else is fair game for
   revision until the protocol stabilizes at v1.0.
